Cape Town - DA MP Phumzile van Damme was at the centre of a social of media storm on Tuesday after she tweeted about an alleged racist incident that took place at the the V&A Waterfront. Van Damme said she had experienced racism and punched one of the offenders in the face in self-defence. "The family. This lady was filming me the entire time, so I tried to take photos & that little s**t in the black t-shirt came to my face & came within my face & [said] â€œvoetsek you blackâ€ & threw [my phone] on the ground. He was threatening violence so in self-defense I punched him in the head," Van Damme tweeted. People had a lot of say about the matter, with reactions ranged from serious to humourous, and many stating that they were not surprised as Cape Town is known for its racism. However, there were many people who couldn't help but make a comparison between the DA MP and action movie star Jean-Claude Van Damme who share the same surname.     Phumzile Van Damme yass girl, that's how we deal with them. pic.twitter.com/2VotWygGeN     We are not surprised. Van Damme is known for throwing punches. #PhumzileVanDamme ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ pic.twitter.com/rIW2F2OxKV     Phumzile is living up to her surname. She is the real van Damme . pic.twitter.com/H3kLJoS0Uu     @JCVD Van Damme is probably wondering why he's trending in SA.And the shock to realize there's a black Van Damme in SA, in 2019. pic.twitter.com/V4WmJBWsMX     A rare picture of Phumzile Van Damme at V&A waterfront ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ pic.twitter.com/mJ1EnHB4TV     Lol bathi Phumzile Van Damme has unleashed the Van Damme in her ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ you are all silly ğŸ˜‚ this time Van Damme didn't use fly kicks but a punch Knockout one ğŸ˜‚ Racists will unleash the real black in you ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚     Phumzile Van Damme was just living up to her surname. You kanti have that last name and not kick ass !!! Chisa .. pic.twitter.com/L84fjMEaBO     Phumzile Van Damme " they don't call me Van Damme for nothing" pic.twitter.com/LbCSAd